
===================================
📌 1. Finglish Version (Persian Latin Script)
===================================

📖 **Tashrih:**
    Dastoor `dh_bash-completion` baraye sakhtan file-haye `bash-completion` baraye dastoorat-e barname-haye shoma estefade mishavad. In dastoor komak mikonad ta karbaran betavanand ba tab zadan (tab completion) dastoorat-e shoma ra asan tar estefade konand.

⚙️ **Gozine-ha:**
    🔹 `--no-guessing`  --> 🤔 Agar kompile nashode bashad, file-haye takmil shodan ra tagheer nadah.
    🔹 `--default-package-name` --> 📦 Esme default package ra moshakhas mikonad. Agar moshakhas nashavad, az `$PACKAGE` estefade mishavad.

🛠 **Mesal-ha:**

    $ dh_bash-completion

    🔹 Sakhtan file-haye `bash-completion` dar directory-haye monaseb.

    $ dh_bash-completion --no-guessing

    🔹 Sakhtan file-haye `bash-completion` be sharti ke ghablan kompile shode bashand.

✅ **Mesal sade:**

    Dar file `debian/rules` khod, ghat'e `dh_bash-completion` ra dar ghat'e `install` ezafe konid.
    In komak mikonad ke dar vaghte build, file-haye `bash-completion` sakhte shavand.

===================================
📌 2. English Version
===================================

📖 **Description:**
    The `dh_bash-completion` command is used to generate `bash-completion` files for your programs' commands. This allows users to more easily use your commands with tab completion.

⚙️ **Options:**
    🔹 `--no-guessing`  --> 🤔 Do not modify completion files if they don't already exist.
    🔹 `--default-package-name` --> 📦 Specifies the default package name. If not specified, it defaults to the `$PACKAGE` variable.

🛠 **Examples:**

    $ dh_bash-completion

    🔹 Generate `bash-completion` files in the appropriate directories.

    $ dh_bash-completion --no-guessing

    🔹 Generate `bash-completion` files only if they already exist.

✅ **Simple Example:**

    In your `debian/rules` file, add `dh_bash-completion` to your `install` target.
    This will make sure that `bash-completion` files are generated at build time.
